[0]Eric Goldman writes "Last month, Utah passed a law [1]banning keyword
advertising. Rep. [2]Dan Eastman, the Utah legislator who sponsored the
law, believes competitive keyword advertising is the equivalent of
corporate identity theft, causing searchers to be ([3]in his words)
'carjacked' and 'shanghaied' by advertisers. He also takes a swipe at the
EFF, dismissing its [4]critique of the law as 'criticism from the
fringes.'"

