|   http://linux.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/10/0252229        |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]kripkenstein writes "openSUSE 10.2 [1]no longer enables ClearType.
(which would improve the appearance of fonts) The reason given on the
openSUSE mailing list for not enabling it is, 'this feature is covered by
several Microsoft patents and should not be activated in any default
build of the library.' As [2]reported on and [3]discussed, this matter
may be connected to the [4]Microsoft-Novell deal. If so, Novell should
have received a license for the Microsoft patents, assuming the deal
covered all relevant patents. Does the license therefore extend only to
SUSE, but not openSUSE?"

