1MC writes "The Chinese govt is requiring game houses to modify MMOG's to
[0]restrict under 18 users to 3 hours "productive" gameplay per day. This
"anti-addiction" software must be in place within 4 months, with games
not compliant by July 15 liable to be shut down in China. Net9, Shanda
and NetEase will be moving to comply with the government regulations.
Users will have to register with their real names and Chinese identity
card numbers to be allowed access to the games."

