+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Internet Radio May Stream North to Canada                          |
|   from the enjoy-your-soundtracks-eh dept.                         |
|   posted by Zonk on Tuesday April 10, @17:57 (The Internet)        |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/10/219231           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "With U.S. copyright royalties threatening to
[0]kill Internet radio in the U.S., Michael Geist explains why webcasters
[1]considering a move to Canada will find that the legal framework for
Internet radio trades costs for complexity. There are two main areas of
concern from a Canadian perspective — broadcast regulation and copyright
fees. The broadcast side is surprisingly regulation-free, but there are
at least three Canadian copyright collectives lining up to collect from
Internet radio stations."

Discuss this story at:
    http://yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/10/219231

