| Radical Transparency at NASA Via Second Life                       |
|   from the gaaames-in-spaaace dept.                                |
|   posted by Zonk on Tuesday April 10, @18:36 (NASA)                |
|   http://games.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/10/2115228        |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "Aaron Rowe over at Wired has an article about
a couple of young scientists at NASA's Ames Research Center [0]working to
open source the space program through [1]software development and other
ways to allow the public to [2]participate in real NASA programs.
According to Robert Schingler, the NASA CoLab project manager, 'CoLab is
building an infrastructure to encourage and facilitate direct
participation from the talented and interested public...' Apparently, the
group holds weekly meetings on their [3]island in the popular online
virtual world [4]Second Life."

